                    <text
                            jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                            sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                            text="&lt;p>Composum Pages provides a number of &lt;a href=&quot;/content/ist/composum/home/pages/development/api/taglibs&quot;>tag libraries&lt;/a> to support creating JSPs , and &lt;a href=&quot;/content/ist/composum/home/pages/development/api/widgets&quot;>dialog widgets&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;for creating editing dialogs. These allow easy creation of custom components for your site. Of course, the Pages editor is implemented using these APIs, and since it's &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ist-dresden/composum-pages&quot;>open source&lt;/a> it also provides quite a number of examples for their use. It uses a &lt;a href=&quot;/content/ist/composum/home/pages/development/api/rest&quot;>REST API&lt;/a> to edit pages, allowing extension of the editor itself if needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>"/>
